  "original_title": "Sri Lanka bond yields edge up; guidance peg steady",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka bond yields edge up; guidance peg steady",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Yields in Sri Lanka\u2019s risk free treasury bonds edged up while treasury bills closed lower on active trade after the weekly bond auction, while\u00a0guidance peg on interbank spot trading remained unchanged on Thursday, dealers said.",
        "The three months\u2019 bill yield closed at 27.00/27.30 percent down\u00a0from Wednesday\u2019sclose at 27.00/28.00 percent.",
        "A bond maturing on 01.06.25 closed at 27.90/28.00 percent up from at 26.30/27.30 percent at last closing.",
        "Sri Lanka sold 50 billion rupees worth of Treasury bonds at a weekly auction on Thursday, data from the state debt office showed.",
        "A guidance peg announced by Sri Lanka\u2019s central bank for interbank transactions remained unchanged at 361.00 rupees against US dollar for a second straight day.",
        "Commercial banks offered dollars for telegraphic transfers at rates between 368.00 and 370.00 for small transactions on July 27, data showed.",
        "Banks offered to buy inward remittances at 358.00 -359.00 rupees. (Colombo/July 28/2022)"
      ],
